Manage Your Flows More Efficiently with the Automation Lightning App
View and monitor your flows in the Automation Lightning app, available to flow admins and users granted access.
Create or open flows from the app.
New list views show recently modified flows and error flows.
Search for flows by keyword in the flow label.
Filter or sort flows by type, status, date, user, and record fields.
Find a direct link to Trailblazer Community and learning material on Trailhead.

This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

In the App Launcher, search for Automation and select the Automation app. If you don’t see the app, go to Process Automation Settings in Setup, and select Enable the Automation Lightning App.
